# {{NAME}} — knowledge skill (project-with-reflect)

A global knowledge module: a reusable practice / recipe / reference that serves many projects.
The content lives in this folder's `{{NAME}}.md` (the folder note); this file is the loader.

## Actions
- **(default) apply** — read `{{NAME}}.md` and apply it to the task at hand. The note is the
  single source of truth; don't improvise around it.
- `update "<content>"` — fold new findings / corrections / tuning into `{{NAME}}.md`: merge +
  dedupe, bounded update — **don't blind-append**. Keep it lean and reader-first (conclusion →
  evidence → reference).
- `note "…"` — force an ephemeral line into `log.md` (a gotcha hit while applying it).
- `reflect` — fold `log.md` into `{{NAME}}.md`, then archive (`reflect.sh archive-entity {{DIR}}`).
- `help` — this menu.

Projects opt in with `/<project> use-knowledge {{NAME}}` (auto-loads when relevant there);
this skill is the from-anywhere handle. Artifacts (images/files) live as siblings in this
folder, embedded `![[<file>]]`.
